text: Lake Matahina is a reservoir in the Bay of Plenty region of New Zealand, located immediately south of the settlement of Te Mahoe and 50 km east of Rotorua. The lake was formed by the construction of the 86 m tall Matahina dam on the Rangitaiki River, which was completed in 1967. ==References== Category:Lakes of the Bay of Plenty Region Category:Reservoirs in New Zealand
